JOB SUMMARY 
The Director of Data Science is a part of our expanding global Data & Analytics team drives data science at ACS. We partner with our business to influence strategy and decision-making and empower our internal customers by providing education and thought leadership on implementing analytics in the business environments. The Director of Data Science is responsible for productize our business intelligence efforts, partner with Digital Marketing team to improve our customer experience, and our research team are effectively using data science tools to deliver amazing insights. In addition, the role follows the Center of Excellence model to help business analysts throughout the Society become more data literate, more capable answering questions and more able to solve problems utilizing data science tools. This role will help grow and lead the team and set the pattern for how data science will be delivered at ACS. 
MAJOR RESPONSIBILITIES 
Leads a team of data analysts, developers, architects supporting internal lines of business 
Chairs the Data Science Center of Excellence and provide education and thought leadership on driving data science at ACS. 
Provides coaching and guidance on data science best practices, not only to your immediate team but also to the entire organization 
Creates robust analytic and data science products in key areas (e.g. Digital Marketing, Population Science, HR, etc.) 
Implements a wide array of analytic techniques including Machine Learning (ML) and Artificial Intelligence (AI) 
Partners with business leadership and execute on project portfolio aimed at business value 
Partners with regional team and digital team to design prototypes and vertical solutions to improve the current customer experience 
Develops and delivers training curriculum on data science leveraging existing tools (e.g. Power BI, Snowflake, SAS, R, etc.) 
Sets financial, operational and quality objectives for the unit and develops master operational plans. Plans, develops and manages departmental expense and capital budgets. 
OTHER FUNCTIONS 
Keep abreast of new trends, and changes in the data science industry. 
Provides status reports and presentations to IT and ACS leadership staff. 
Undertakes specialized projects, studies, and assignments as requested by IT and ACS leadership team. 
 
Position Requirements: 
